    "The collective findings underscore the importance of ethical considerations in the fields of ICT and Software Engineering.",
    "A number of secondary studies have been conducted that focused on the theme of investigating the ethical principles and guidelines related to AI.",
    "For example, Khan et al. (2022) conducted a Systematic Literature Review (SLR) to investigate the agreement on the significance of AI ethical principles and identify potential challenges to their adoption.",
    "They found that the most common AI ethics principles are transparency, privacy, accountability, and fairness.",
    "However, significant challenges in incorporating ethics into AI include a lack of ethical knowledge and vague principles."
